I don’t really feel the loudspeaker and turning people into vomit ideas were really married well for me. I think part of it comes from the interview reading weird, with the mix of childlike sentiment and big words that felt out of place such as “fascinating” and “smokestack” making it not really sound like a kid. I don’t know if you were intending for that dichotomy to be there but it didn’t add anything to the article for me. I think with some additional development to make the concepts blend more smoothly this could be pretty cool. For now I’m downvoting.








